<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>Challenge Prioritization Matrix</h1>
            <div class="subtitle">Business Risk vs. Current Pain Level</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="instructions">
            <strong>How to use this tool:</strong> Drag challenge categories from the left onto the matrix. Place them based on:
            <br><br>
            <strong>Y-axis (Business Risk):</strong> How much this problem costs you (money, time, customer trust, employee morale)
            <br>
            <strong>X-axis (Current Pain Level):</strong> How much this problem is hurting your team right now (frustration, daily friction, operational pain)
        </div>

        <div class="matrix-container">
            <div class="chips-container">
                <div class="chips-header">Challenge Categories</div>
                <div id="chipsList">
                    <div class="chip" draggable="true" data-id="1">Alignment & Getting on the Same Page</div>
                    <div class="chip" draggable="true" data-id="2">Process Breakdowns & Bottlenecks</div>
                    <div class="chip" draggable="true" data-id="3">Handoffs & Communication Gaps</div>
                    <div class="chip" draggable="true" data-id="4">People Working Around the System</div>
                    <div class="chip" draggable="true" data-id="5">Scaling & Growth Pains</div>
                    <div class="chip" draggable="true" data-id="6">Technology & System Integration</div>
